(UNITED STATES OF AMERICA, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. MARIA DEL REFUGIO RODRIGUEZ-RAMIREZ, Defendant-Appellant, 1-10, Lexis)

Arizona Revised Statute section 13-3405(A)(2) provides that HN4&amp;#34;A person shall not knowingly. . . Possess marijuana for sale.&amp;#34; (emphasis added). In the instant case, the district court determined that the preposition &amp;#34;for&amp;#34; in the phrase &amp;#34;for sale&amp;#34; is an express statement of intention, i.e. one cannot possess anything &amp;#34;for sale&amp;#34; absent an intent to sell it.
