(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
AND

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
be more than just a possibility, whatever promises had been made.”48

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;margin-top:10.0pt;mso-pagination:widow-orphan lines-together; page-break-after:avoid;mso-outline-level:4&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;;mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun;mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;mso-bidi-theme-font:major-bidi; mso-bidi-font-style:italic&amp;#34; %)**__Unintentional release__**(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;; mso-fareast-font-family:SimSun;mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;mso-bidi-theme-font: major-bidi;mso-bidi-font-style:italic&amp;#34; %)** risk is high ~-~~-~- especially for smallpox**

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt; font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;&amp;#34; %)**Breman 3**(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;&amp;#34; %) – Joel G., MD, et al., “Preventing the Return of Smallpox”, New England Journal of Medicine, 348(5), 1-30, http:~/~/info.med.yale.edu/eph/pdf/biotarticles.1/NEJM-smallpox/Preventing.pdf

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt; font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;&amp;#34; %) 

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
It is imperative and urgent that we prevent the intentional or unintentional release of variola

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
AND

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
has been confirmed to have smallpox virus, but the rumors persist.15

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;margin-top:10.0pt;mso-pagination:widow-orphan lines-together; page-break-after:avoid;mso-outline-level:4&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;;mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun;mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;mso-bidi-theme-font:major-bidi; mso-bidi-font-style:italic&amp;#34; %)**Extinction**

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:14.0pt; font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-style: italic&amp;#34; %)**Singer 1**(% style=&amp;#34;font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt;font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;&amp;#34; %) – Clifford E., Professor of Nuclear Engineering and Director of the Program in Arms Control, Disarmament, and International Security – University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, “Will Mankind Survive the Millennium?”, http:~/~/www.acdis.uiuc.edu/research/SandPs/2001-Sp/SandP_XIII/Singer.htm

