Development of a compact, non-fission trigger poses a significant technical challenge – requiring vast sums of money and significant political commitment.
Nevertheless, fusion research is proceeding. Experiments are currently being conducted in at least 17 nations, with one of two goals:
1. Harnessing fusion for electrical power generation;
2. Replicating conditions of a nuclear explosion at the moment of detonation to test for warhead reliability.
Regardless of intent, this research could unlock the key to achieving compact, non-fission &amp;#34;ignition&amp;#34; of thermonuclear fuel – paving the way for possible FGNW development.
